01:08:42.479 --> 01:08:44.146
involved derivatives
of the metric times

01:08:44.146 --> 01:08:45.765
derivative of the metric.

01:08:45.765 --> 01:08:47.640
Many of you may have
heard sort of the slogan

01:08:47.640 --> 01:08:50.890
that general relativity is a
nonlinear theory of gravity.

01:08:50.890 --> 01:08:52.770
There's where your
nonlinearity is actually

01:08:52.770 --> 01:08:54.145
going to turn out
to be entering,

01:08:54.145 --> 01:08:57.000
is the fact you add these
squared terms in here that

01:08:57.000 --> 01:08:59.130
involve metric times
itself entering

01:08:59.130 --> 01:09:02.827
in such a non-trivial
and important way.

01:09:02.827 --> 01:09:04.410
What I'm going to
do, finally, on this

01:09:04.410 --> 01:09:06.029
is-- so this is
slightly annoying

01:09:06.029 --> 01:09:08.859
because I have one term
